20chatbots%20and%20emails%20and%20FAQs%20and%20some%20good%20old%20figure-it-out-on-your-own%20nudges%2C%20all%20in%20the%20name%20of%20efficiency%20and%2C%20ultimately%2C%20profits.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcvs-pharmacy-use-ai-customer-service-call-centers-tilak-mandadi-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECompanies%20are%20now%20claiming%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-take-anger-out-customer-complaints-call-centers-softbank-japan-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20will%20fix%20this%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20we%20should%20hold%20our%20collective%20breath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20midst%20of%20all%20this%2C%20the%20phone%20call%20has%20become%20a%20status%20symbol%20of%20sorts.%20You%20want%20to%20speak%20to%20a%20representative%3F%20That's%20a%20privilege%2C%20not%20a%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20have%20made%20it%20so%20difficult%20to%20talk%20to%20a%20person%20that%20customers%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20younger%20people%20%E2%80%94%20have%20started%20to%20internalize%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20phone%20call%20as%20a%20premium%20product.%20Gen%20Zers%20don't%20like%20to%20talk%20on%20the%20phone%2C%20except%20when%20it%20makes%20them%20feel%20exclusive%20and%20important.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fcapabilities%2Foperations%2Four-insights%2Foperations-blog%2Fwhy-your-kids-arent-calling-you-but-they-are-calling-their-bank%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcKinsey%20recently%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20when%20Gen%20Zers%20were%20engaging%20with%20premium%20brands%20or%20services%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-express-platinum-card-gold-gen-z-millennial-rewards-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20fancy%20American%20Express%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20they%20were%20actually%20more%20likely%20to%20make%20a%20call%20than%20millennials%20and%20as%20likely%20to%20call%20as%20boomers.%20They%20see%20the%20ability%20to%20call%20as%20a%20concierge-like%20service%20that%20helps%20them%20skip%20to%20the%20front%20of%20the%20line%20and%20offload%20the%20labor%20of%20whatever%20they're%20trying%20to%20accomplish%20onto%20someone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20verbatims%20we%20heard%20were%20things%20like%2C%20'Well%2C%20if%20I'm%20paying%20%24500%20for%20a%20premium%20card%20from%20Barclays%20or%20Amex%20or%20whatnot%2C%20then%20part%20of%20the%20service%20for%20me%20is%20phone%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Eric%20Buesing%2C%20a%20partner%20at%20McKinsey%20who%20advises%20clients%20in%20banking%20and%20financial%20services.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20generation%20that's%20always%20grown%20up%20with%20digital%20and%20not%20the%20transition%20to%20digital%2C%20and%20therefore%20the%20phone%20is%20not%20more%20of%20a%20legacy%2C%20it's%20more%20of%20an%20assistant%2C%20somebody%20that%20will%20just%20do%20it%20for%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGen%20Zers%20aren't%20wrong%20in%20their%20assessment%20that%20the%20phone%20is%20a%20perk.%20It's%20a%20fact%20of%20life%20across%20the%20consumer%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you've%20ever%20experienced%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflying-delays-cancellations-passenger-airlines-air-travel-rights-refunds-fees-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eflying%20snafu%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20traveling%20with%20people%20who%20have%20various%20airline%20statuses%2C%20you%20may%20have%20noticed%20some%20of%20your%20fellow%20travelers%20had%20a%20much%20easier%20time%20getting%20their%20flight%20rerouted%20or%20their%20baggage%20found.%20That's%20not%20an%20accident%3A%20Airlines%20used%20to%20have%20separate%20phone%20numbers%20for%20elites%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20they%20still%20do%20%E2%80%94%20but%20now%2C%20even%20if%20high-status%20passengers%20don't%20know%20the%20magic%20number%2C%20they%20get%20sorted%20into%20better%20and%20faster%20phone%20service%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20top%20tiers%20of%20elite%20status%20do%20give%20you%20access%20to%20special%20phone%20numbers%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Clint%20Henderson%2C%20a%20managing%20editor%20at%20The%20Points%20Guy%2C%20a%20travel%20blog%20and%20website.%20%26quot%3BThey%20also%20know%20your%20phone%20number%20when%20you're%20calling%2C%20so%20they'll%20route%20you%20to%20a%20quicker%20queue.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHenderson%20lamented%20that%20this%20passenger%20caste%20system%20isn't%20as%20good%20as%20it%20used%20to%20be%20%E2%80%94%20for%20the%20winners%2C%20obviously.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20you%20got%20%3Cem%3Ereally%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Especialized%3C%2Fem%3E%20call%20desks%20and%20agents%20who%20could%20go%20extraordinarily%20above%20and%20beyond%20if%20you%20were%20lucky%20(and%20spent%20enough).%20Now%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-travel-airline-customer-service-airports-delayed-canceled-flights-terrible-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eairline%20cost-cutting%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20even%20come%20for%20elite%20travelers.%20Still%2C%20they're%20getting%20a%20much%20better%20deal%20on%20the%20phone%20than%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20used%20to%20be%20really%2C%20really%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20Henderson%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20now%20it's%20just%20really%20nice%20to%20have%2C%20especially%20when%20there's%20a%20meltdown%20or%20something%2C%20because%20you're%20going%20to%20get%20priority%20for%20callbacks%20and%20for%20rebooking.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20just%20airlines%20%E2%80%94%20plenty%20of%20companies%20are%20great%20at%20finding%20all%20kinds%20of%20ways%20to%20sort%20customers%20into%20priority%20levels%2C%20including%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20phone.%20Verizon%2C%20for%20example%2C%20charges%20a%20%2410%20%26quot%3Bagent%20assistance%20fee%26quot%3B%20when%20you%20pay%20your%20bill%20by%20calling%20its%20customer-service%20line.%20AT%26amp%3BT%20and%20T-Mobile%20charge%20to%20pay%20via%20human%2C%20too.%20The%20only%20way%20to%20get%20live%20phone%20support%2024%2F7%20from%20Yahoo%20is%20by%20paying.%20(I%20am%20not%20entirely%20sure%20how%20many%20people%20need%20to%20call%20Yahoo%20these%20days%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Fyahoo%2Fcomments%2Funcvy3%2Fcustomer_service_is_a_paid_subscription%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Reddit%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20is%20an%20issue%20people%20have%20encountered.)%20Best%20Buy's%2024%2F7%20phone%20tech%20support%20is%20available%20as%20part%20of%20a%20package%20that%20costs%20%24180%20annually%20%E2%80%94%20something%20it%20took%20me%20a%20lengthy%20back-and-forth%20with%20a%20chat%20assistant%20to%20figure%20out.%20(Best%20Buy%20points%20out%20that%20package%20has%20other%20features%20and%20that%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20free%20ways%20to%20connect%20with%20its%20agents.)%20AppleCare%2B%20gets%20you%20priority%20phone%20access.%20Fidelity%20has%20various%20tiers%20of%20advisory%20services.%20You%20may%20be%20able%20to%20get%20someone%20on%20the%20phone%20at%20a%20lower%20tier%2C%20depending%20what%20you%20need%2C%20but%20to%20get%20phone%20access%20to%20a%20dedicated%20team%20of%20advisors%2C%20you%20have%20to%20invest%20%2450%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsumers%20are%20frustrated%20that%20access%20to%20a%20human%20is%20on%20the%20decline%20%E2%80%94%20that%20extreme%20corporate%20frugality%20has%20rendered%20hearing%20a%20voice%20on%20the%20other%20end%20of%20the%20line%20a%20novelty.%20Simultaneously%2C%20those%20with%20premium%20status%20have%20come%20to%2C%20probably%20fairly%2C%20believe%20that%20spending%20so%20much%20money%20entitles%20them%20to%20a%20level%20of%20direct%20access%20that's%20become%20scarce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20becomes%20really%20easy%20for%20companies%20to%20start%20positioning%20the%20access%20to%20phone%20service%20as%20a%20premium%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Michelle%20Kinch%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20of%20business%20administration%20at%20Dartmouth's%20Tuck%20School%20of%20Business.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20expensive%2C%20and%20so%20therefore%20you've%20got%20to%20have%20the%20revenue%20associated%20with%20that%20to%20make%20it%20a%20profitable%20part%20of%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20just%20kind%20of%20boils%20down%20to%20that%20cost-benefit.%20If%20I%2C%20as%20a%20company%2C%20can%20calculate%20what%20my%20customer%20profitability%20is%2C%20then%20I%20can%20determine%20where%20I%20could%20deploy%20those%20more%20expensive%20resources%2C%20particularly%20if%20I'm%20going%20to%20engender%20higher%20levels%20of%20loyalty%20from%20the%20customer%20as%20a%20result.%20It%20becomes%20a%20perk.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKinch's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hbs.edu%2Fris%2FPublication%2520Files%2F19-089_41436e5b-f067-4040-9281-5069a1474b3d.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20impact%20of%20increasingly%20sterile%20customer%20service%20on%20the%20consumer%20psyche%20has%20found%20that%20lacking%20human%20contact%20can%20make%20an%20already%20anxiety-inducing%20situation%20worse.%20When%20people%20are%20on%20edge%20%E2%80%94%20which%20they%20often%20are%20when%20they're%20trying%20to%20reach%20a%20representative%20%E2%80%94%20they%20crave%20human%20contact.%20Just%20the%20reassurance%20that%20they%20%3Cem%3Ecould%3C%2Fem%3E%20talk%20to%20someone%20if%20they%20wanted%20makes%20them%20feel%20better.%20She's%20recently%20been%20working%20on%20a%20small-scale%20study%20on%20AI%20in%20customer%20service%20and%20has%20observed%20that%20people%20interacting%20with%20virtual%20agents%20reported%20feeling%20more%20anxious%20immediately%20after%20those%20interactions%20than%20those%20who%20dealt%20with%20people.%20Anecdotally%2C%20it%20tracks%20%E2%80%94%20plenty%20of%20people%20have%20had%20the%20experience%20of%2C%20say%2C%20confirming%20a%20credit-card%20charge%20with%20a%20bot%20and%20then%20wondering%20if%20that%20confirmation%20stuck.%20And%20in%20a%20high-anxiety%20situation%2C%20like%20dealing%20with%20a%20travel%20cancellation%20or%20making%20a%20financial%20transaction%2C%20people%20just%20really%20want%20the%20option%20to%20talk%20to%20someone%20if%20they%20need%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20that%20old%20adage%20that%20misery%20loves%20company%20for%20a%20reason%2C%26quot%3B%20Kinch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20recently%20experienced%20a%20pay-to-phone%20conundrum%20with%20a%20prominent%20research%20platform.%20She%20switched%20jobs%20and%20got%20locked%20out%20of%20her%20old%20email%2C%20and%20the%20only%20way%20for%20her%20to%20call%20customer%20service%20about%20the%20problem%20was%20to%20pay%20for%20a%20subscription.%20Even%20the%20person%20on%20the%20phone%20couldn't%20solve%20her%20issue%2C%20but%20she%20had%20to%20keep%20paying%20to%20subscribe%20because%20the%20only%20way%20to%20close%20her%20account%20was%20over%20the%20phone%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20aren't%20many%20obvious%20solutions%20here.%20Buesing%2C%20from%20McKinsey%2C%20said%20call%20volumes%20were%20going%20up%20at%20many%20organizations%2C%20meaning%20the%20need%20for%20human%20contact%20isn't%20going%20away.%20He's%20talking%20to%20his%20clients%20about%20introducing%20premium%20chatbots%20to%20solve%20customers'%20problems.%20That%20could%20perhaps%20be%20nice%20for%20people%20who%20access%20them%2C%20though%20given%20the%20state%20of%20the%20chatbot%2C%20which%20is%20mediocre%20at%20best%2C%20it's%20hard%20to%20imagine%20exactly%20how%20a%20chatbot%20could%20achieve%20premium%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20could%2C%20of%20course%2C%20invest%20more%20in%20call%20centers%20and%20hire%20people%20to%20talk%20to%20customers%2C%20but%20that%20would%20require%20them%20to%20do%20something%20they%20would%20very%20much%20like%20to%20avoid%3A%20spend%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20the%20phone%20feels%20fancy%20is%20that%20it%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20fancy%2C%20or%20at%20least%20a%20relief.%20Sometimes%20you%20want%20to%20explain%20your%20issue%20to%20someone%20(without%20yelling%20or%20being%20mean%2C%20eh)%20and%20get%20it%20figured%20out%20and%20taken%20care%20of.%20The%20phone%20may%20have%20become%20a%20status%20symbol%2C%20but%20it%20shouldn't%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomer-service-phone-calls-paid-status-symbol-luxury-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725443162000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d097f6392a3bda9f231c22%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomer-service-phone-calls-paid-status-symbol-luxury-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20age%20of%20customer%20service%20chatbots%20and%20endless%20FAQs%2C%20the%20ability%20to%20speak%20to%20a%20real%20human%20being%20is%20a%20luxury.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22estewart%40insider.com%20(Emily%20Stewart)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomer-service-phone-calls-paid-status-symbol-luxury-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22EPS%20pensioners%20take%20note!%20Now%2C%20get%20pension%20from%20any%20bank%2C%20any%20branch%E2%80%A6%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725443049000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-113060144%2Cimgsize-92372.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fbusiness%2Findia-business%2Fgood-news-for-eps-pensioners-now-get-pension-from-any-bank-any-branch-anywhere-in-india-from-january-1-2025%2Farticleshow%2F113059993.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Union%20Minister%20of%20Labour%20and%20Employment%20has%20approved%20a%20Centralized%20Pension%20Payment%20System%20(CPPS)%20for%20the%20Employees'%20Pension%20Scheme%2C%201995.%20From%20January%201%2C%202025%2C%20pensioners%20will%20be%20able%20to%20receive%20their%20pensions%20from%20any%20bank%20branch%20across%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20BUSINESS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22All%20About%20PresVu%2C%20New%20Eye%20Drops%20That%20Can%20Remove%20Reading%20Glasses%20In%2015%20Mins%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Drugs%20Controller%20General%20of%20India%20has%20approved%20Entod%20Pharmaceuticals'%20PresVu%20eye%20drops%2C%20which%20is%20said%20to%20be%20a%20breakthrough%20in%20the%20treatment%20of%20presbyopia.%20The%20pharmaceutical%20company%20has%20already%20received%20approval%20for%20the%20eye%20drop%20from%20the%20Subject%20Expert%20Committee%20of%20the%20Central%20Drugs%20Standard%20Control%20Organization%20(CDSCO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresVu%20is%20India's%20first%20eye%20drop%2C%20specially%20made%20for%20individuals%20suffering%20from%20presbyopia%20who%20are%20forced%20to%20read%20with%20glasses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Is%20Presbyopia%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresbyopia%20is%20an%20age-related%20condition%20that%20makes%20it%20difficult%20to%20focus%20on%20near%20objects.%20Generally%2C%20people%20above%2040%20years%20of%20age%20suffer%20from%20this%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%2C%201.09%20billion%20to%201.80%20billion%20people%20globally%20are%20estimated%20to%20be%20suffering%20from%20presbyopia%2C%20highlighting%20the%20massive%20impact%20of%20this%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresbyopia%20occurs%20naturally%20with%20ageing%20as%20the%20eye's%20ability%20to%20focus%20declines.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20condition%20can%20have%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20a%20person's%20quality%20of%20life%2C%20affecting%20their%20ability%20to%20perform%20everyday%20tasks%20and%20maintain%20their%20lifestyle.%20Many%20realise%20they%20have%20presbyopia%20when%20they%20try%20to%20hold%20reading%20objects%20at%20arm's%20length%20to%20see%20clearly.%20It%20can%20be%20detected%20by%20a%20simple%20examination%20of%20the%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20about%20PresVu%2C%20Nikhil%20K%20Masurkar%2C%20CEO%2C%20Entod%20Pharmaceuticals%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BPresVu%20has%20been%20created%20through%20years%20of%20research%20and%20development.%20Its%20approval%20by%20DCGI%20is%20a%20major%20step%20in%20our%20mission%20to%20transform%20eye%20care%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPresVu%3A%20Key%20Benefits%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEntod%20Pharmaceuticals%20has%20applied%20for%20a%20patent%20regarding%20the%20formulation%20and%20process%20of%20PresVu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEntod's%20formula%20not%20only%20provides%20relief%20from%20reading%20glasses%20but%20also%20gives%20an%20additional%20benefit%20to%20the%20patient%20--%20it%20helps%20lubricate%20the%20eyes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20formula%20uses%20advanced%20dynamic%20buffer%20technology%20to%20rapidly%20adapt%20to%20the%20pH%20of%20tears.%20Its%20effect%20remains%20for%20a%20longer%20duration%2C%20while%20the%20eyes%20also%20remain%20protected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENikkhil%20K%20Masurkar%2C%20CEO%2C%20Entod%20Pharmaceuticals%20noted%20that%20PresVu%20was%20created%20after%20years%20of%20research%20and%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20DCGI%20approval%20is%20a%20major%20step%20forward%20in%20our%20mission%20to%20transform%20eye%20care%20in%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMasurkar%20noted%20that%20PresVu%20is%20more%20than%20just%20a%20product%3B%20it's%20a%20solution%20that%20works%20to%20improve%20the%20lives%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20by%20helping%20them%20see%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Enhances%20Near%20Vision%20In%2015%20minutes'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20benefits%20of%20PresVu%20for%20patients%2C%20Dr%20Aditya%20Sethi%20noted%20that%20Presbyopia%20has%20long%20been%20treated%20with%20reading%20glasses%2C%20contact%20lenses%20and%20surgical%20measures.%20With%20PresVu%2C%20it%20can%20be%20treated%20effectively%20as%20the%20eye%20drop%20improves%20near%20vision%20within%2015%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20treatment%20can%20significantly%20improve%20the%20quality%20of%20life%20for%20many%20people%2C%20allowing%20them%20to%20perform%20everyday%20tasks%20easily%2C%20he%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20doctor%20further%20noted%20that%20it%20was%20important%20to%20monitor%20symptoms%20and%20consult%20a%20doctor%20if%20blurred%20near%20vision%20interferes%20with%20reading%20or%20other%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommenting%20on%20the%20clinical%20potential%20of%20PresVu%2C%20Dr%20Dhananjay%20Bakhle%20said%20its%20approval%20was%20a%20promising%20achievement%20in%20the%20field%20of%20ophthalmology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20presbyopia%20patients%2C%20this%20eye%20drop%20provides%20a%20non-invasive%20option%20that%20eliminates%20the%20need%20for%20reading%20glasses%2C%20he%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725443040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-09%2F4lq6keso_eye-drop-generic_625x300_04_September_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fall-about-presvu-new-eye-drops-that-can-remove-reading-glasses-in-15-mins-6488271%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Drugs%20Controller%20General%20of%20India%20has%20approved%20Entod%20Pharmaceuticals'%20PresVu%20eye%20drops%2C%20which%20is%20said%20to%20be%20a%20breakthrough%20in%20the%20treat