and%20landslides.%C2%A0The%20disasters%20reportedly%20resulted%20in%20approximately%201%2C000%20deaths.%20According%20to%20a%20report%20by%20South%20Korea's%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.tvchosun.com%2Fsite%2Fdata%2Fhtml_dir%2F2024%2F09%2F03%2F2024090390229.html%5C%22%3EChosun%20TV%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20citing%20a%20North%20Korean%20official%2C%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20called%20for%20''strict%20punishment''%20to%20be%20meted%20out%20to%20those%20deemed%20responsible%20for%20the%20''unacceptable%20loss''%20of%20life%20caused%20by%20the%20recent%20flooding.%C2%A0Officials%20were%20also%20charged%20with%20corruption%20and%20dereliction%20of%20duty.%C2%A0The%20executions%20reportedly%20took%20place%20late%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E''It%20has%20been%20determined%20that%2020%20to%2030%20cadres%20in%20the%20flood-stricken%20area%20were%20executed%20at%20the%20same%20time%20late%20last%20month%2C''%20the%20official%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20identities%20of%20the%20executed%20officials%20remain%20undisclosed%2C%20the%20North%20Korean%20Central%20News%20Agency%20(KCNA)%20reported%20that%20Kang%20Bong-hoon%2C%20the%20secretary%20of%20the%20Chagang%20Province%20Provincial%20Party%20Committee%20since%202019%2C%20was%20among%20the%20leaders%20removed%20from%20their%20positions%20by%20Kim%20Jong-un.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%2C%20severe%20rainfall%20triggered%20landslides%20and%20flooding%20in%20North%20Korea%2C%20affecting%20over%204%2C000%20homes%20and%20leaving%2015%2C000%20residents%20displaced.%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20himself%20visited%20the%20affected%20areas%20and%20stated%20that%20it%20would%20take%20several%20months%20to%20rebuild%20and%20restore%20the%20neighbourhoods%20that%20were%20completely%20inundated%20by%20the%20floods.%20The%20government%20also%20provided%20shelter%20in%20Pyongyang%20facilities%20for%2015%2C400%20people%2C%20including%20vulnerable%20groups%20such%20as%20mothers%2C%20children%2C%20the%20elderly%2C%20and%20disabled%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20North%20Korean%20leader%20denied%20reports%20of%20a%20high%20death%20toll%20from%20the%20flooding%2C%20dismissing%20the%20claims%20as%20%26quot%3Bfalse%20rumours.%26quot%3B%20He%20accused%20South%20Korea%20of%20spreading%20these%20rumours%20as%20part%20of%20a%20deliberate%20%26quot%3Bsmear%20campaign%26quot%3B%20designed%20to%20damage%20North%20Korea's%20international%20reputation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELee%20Il-gyu%2C%20a%20former%20North%20Korean%20diplomat%20at%20the%20International%20Korean%20Peninsula%20Forum%20remarked%2C%20%26quot%3BEven%20though%20there%20was%20recent%20flood%20damage%2C%20they%20were%20dismissed%20for%20social%20security%20reasons%2C%20and%20the%20executives%20themselves%20are%20so%20anxious%20that%20they%20don't%20know%20when%20their%20necks%20will%20fall%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2C%20noindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.koreatimes.co.kr%2Fwww%2Fnation%2F2024%2F09%2F103_361356.html%5C%22%3EKorea%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20North%20Korea's%20public%20executions%20have%20surged%20dramatically%20since%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%20Before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20country%20typically%20saw%20around%2010%20public%20executions%20per%20year.%20However%2C%20that%20number%20has%20skyrocketed%20to%20approximately%20100%20annual%20public%20executions%2C%20representing%20a%20tenfold%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1725429360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2F2885brr4_kim-jong-un_625x300_11_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fkim-jong-un-executes-30-officials-for-failing-to-prevent-deaths-during-floods-report-6486649%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20July%2C%20severe%20rainfall%20triggered%20landslides%20and%20flooding%20in%20North%20Kore